          "type": "set_variable",
          "_nested_name": "home_practice_challenges.text_challenge_2"
        },
        {
          "name": "reply_challenge_2",
          "value": "When your teen gets angry, you might need to walk away until you are both calm. \n\nCheck to make sure your consequence is fair and reasonable. Listen to your teen’s explanation, and make sure to give a “Safety Amnesty” if they broke a rule in order to stay safe.",
